Sentencas: Semiconductor heterostructure SrTiO3/CeO2 (STO/CeO2) membrane was used as the electrolyte material of low-temperature solid oxide fuel cells.
Titulo: Semiconductor Heterostructure SrTiO3/CeO2 Electrolyte Membrane Fuel Cells

Sentencas: This STO/CeO2 membrane demonstrated a high ionic conductivity of 0.24 S cm(-1) under fuel cell conditions at 550 degrees C, and also its fuel cell delivered a maximum power output of 745.6 mW cm(-2) at the same temperature.
Titulo: Semiconductor Heterostructure SrTiO3/CeO2 Electrolyte Membrane Fuel Cells

Sentencas: Moreover, the high electronic conductivity of CeO2 is blocked by the STO/CeO2 semiconductor heterojunction, thus resulting in the open circuit voltage increasing from 0.90 to 1.09 V at 550 degrees C.
Titulo: Semiconductor Heterostructure SrTiO3/CeO2 Electrolyte Membrane Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The semiconductor heterointerface is found to play an important role in inhibiting the electron transfer between CeO2 particles.
Titulo: Semiconductor Heterostructure SrTiO3/CeO2 Electrolyte Membrane Fuel Cells

Sentencas: Thus, this work makes it feasibility of using semiconductor materials as the electrolyte by constructing heterojunctions to suppress the electronic conductivity.
Titulo: Semiconductor Heterostructure SrTiO3/CeO2 Electrolyte Membrane Fuel Cells
